copy/link this directory inside the PLUGIN folder of any (recent)
version of MG5_aMC (2.8+)

to generate a process, run MG5_aMC as usual, and specify pyout as output format 
./bin/mg5

generate g g > t t~
output pyout FOLDER_NAME

## Install plugin in madgraph

In order to install the madflow plugin in madgraph, it is necessary to link the `madgraph_plugin` folder inside the `PLUGIN` directory of Madgraph.
For instance, if the environmental variable `$MADGRAPH_PATH` is pointing to the madgraph root:

```bash
    ~$ ln -s ${PWD}/madgraph_plugin ${MADGRAPH_PATH}/PLUGIN/pyout
```
